(MYGN), a leader in molecular diagnostics and personalized medicine, is working to educate the public about hereditary cancer risk assessment and testing during Prostate Cancer Awareness Month this September.  With 2.9 million men living with prostate cancer, it is now the second leading form of cancer in the United States, killing one man every 19 minutes.  Up to 15 percent of prostate cancers are due to an inherited mutation.  Myriad's myRisk® Hereditary Cancer test is an effective tool to assess genetic mutations in men diagnosed with prostate cancer.
